WEBVTT

00:05.614 --> 00:08.834
♪

00:08.878 --> 00:11.141
Lord, I always put
my trust in you.

00:12.142 --> 00:13.796
I made a big leap of faith,

00:13.839 --> 00:15.841
and I thought it was
the right thing.

00:15.885 --> 00:19.541
But I find myself 30 years
in the future and...

00:20.759 --> 00:22.805
...I've experienced
the impossible.

00:22.848 --> 00:24.328
[indistinct radio chatter]

00:27.549 --> 00:29.638
Why are the taking
the BestTime snacks?

00:29.681 --> 00:31.640
They took the piano, too.

00:31.683 --> 00:33.468
They're punishing us.

00:33.511 --> 00:35.165
For Shanice escaping.

00:35.209 --> 00:37.950
[sighs] We've got
to get out of here.

00:37.994 --> 00:39.822
REV:
I asked you for a sign.

00:39.865 --> 00:41.737
This must be the sign,

00:41.780 --> 00:44.696
but... help me understand.

00:44.740 --> 00:46.785
What am I to do?

00:48.961 --> 00:50.572
STEVE:
Hey.

00:50.615 --> 00:52.791
They need to
talk to you.

00:52.835 --> 00:54.663
You want to tell us
how you escaped

00:54.706 --> 00:56.012
from the hotel
the other day?

00:56.056 --> 00:57.100
Do you want to tell me
when you plan on

00:57.144 --> 00:58.362
letting us out of here for good?

00:58.406 --> 00:59.972
Since as far as I can tell,
you have

01:00.016 --> 01:02.192
no lawful grounds to detain us.

01:02.236 --> 01:03.846
You took a huge risk.

01:03.889 --> 01:06.022
Potentially exposing
your husband and daughter...

01:06.066 --> 01:08.111
To what? They're my family.

01:08.155 --> 01:10.070
Look, Shanice,
you know we're not the enemy.

01:10.113 --> 01:12.376
Michigan Penal Code,
Article 328.

01:12.420 --> 01:14.987
"A person who commits
unlawful imprisonment

01:15.031 --> 01:17.251
is guilty of a felony."

01:17.294 --> 01:19.035
Just tell us
who you were working with.

01:19.079 --> 01:20.732
Are they the same ones
who leaked to the public

01:20.776 --> 01:22.386
that you all
are missing persons?

01:22.430 --> 01:24.040
That there are 4,400 of you?

01:25.650 --> 01:27.652
"Punishable...

01:27.696 --> 01:30.133
"by not more than 15 years

01:30.177 --> 01:33.745
or a fine of not more
than $20,000, or both."

01:33.789 --> 01:35.791
So have you all figured out
how we apparently

01:35.834 --> 01:37.532
travelled through time?

01:37.575 --> 01:40.839
We don't know that's
what happened.

01:40.883 --> 01:42.798
So how come the last thing
I remember

01:42.841 --> 01:44.321
it was 2015...

01:44.365 --> 01:46.454
and now it's 2021?

01:46.497 --> 01:48.673
Maybe you were
taken somewhere?

01:48.717 --> 01:51.372
Maybe someone doesn't
want you to remember?Ew, who?

01:51.415 --> 01:53.635
Well, that's what we want to
find out, but most importantly,

01:53.678 --> 01:55.637
we want to make sure
that everybody's okay now.

01:55.680 --> 01:57.639
Okay, well, we'd be more okay
if we could get out of here.

01:57.682 --> 01:59.162
And if we didn't have to wear

01:59.206 --> 02:01.338
these truly hideous
synthetic fabrics.

02:01.382 --> 02:03.166
Like, can you do something
about this...

02:03.210 --> 02:04.341
travesty?

02:04.385 --> 02:05.777
MILDRED:
Uh...

02:07.039 --> 02:09.433
I don't know anything
about how Shanice got out.

02:09.477 --> 02:11.479
Really? Because
she was last seen

02:11.522 --> 02:12.915
headed to the
bathroom with you.

02:12.958 --> 02:14.395
JHARREL:
Yo.

02:14.438 --> 02:16.179
She's just a kid.And kids lie, too.

02:16.223 --> 02:17.746
JHARREL: Okay, you really
think interrogating minors is

02:17.789 --> 02:19.835
is the best way to figure...

02:19.878 --> 02:21.358
[Jharrel grunts]

02:22.968 --> 02:24.883
Well, I think we were just
about done here anyway.

02:24.927 --> 02:27.930
Hey, come on, I'll have one
of the guards take you back.

02:29.627 --> 02:31.977
Why did you say what you
said the other night?

02:32.021 --> 02:33.892
You said to tell
Jharrel that...

02:33.936 --> 02:36.112
Manny's all right, that
he's sorry for everything.

02:36.156 --> 02:37.853
How do you know
Jharrel's brother?

02:37.896 --> 02:39.159
I don't know him.

02:39.202 --> 02:41.030
Then why were you talking
about him?

02:41.073 --> 02:43.554
Does it have something to do
with why you all are here?

02:43.598 --> 02:46.078
No. I-I-I guess it was
just something I heard.

02:46.122 --> 02:47.950
From who? From Jharrel?

02:47.993 --> 02:49.691
No. Just...

02:49.734 --> 02:52.041
people talk.

02:52.084 --> 02:54.130
So it was what... a prank?

02:54.174 --> 02:56.393
Is this whole thing
some kind of prank?

02:57.525 --> 02:59.222
We are trying to help you all.

02:59.266 --> 03:01.442
You need to be honest with
us, not jerk us around...

03:01.485 --> 03:02.965
Look, I can't eat the new food.

03:04.096 --> 03:06.098
And they took away
the BestTime Bars.

03:07.317 --> 03:09.493
I love the BestTime Bars.

03:11.495 --> 03:13.541
I've cooperated
since we've got here.

03:13.584 --> 03:15.586
But there has been
no movement to get us out.

03:15.630 --> 03:18.067
It would help if people
weren't leaking information

03:18.110 --> 03:19.460
to the press
and escaping custody.

03:19.503 --> 03:21.331
Those sound like your problems.

03:21.375 --> 03:22.593
Not mine.

03:22.637 --> 03:24.987
And what is your
problem, Reverend?

03:25.030 --> 03:27.250
I lost something that night.

03:27.294 --> 03:28.991
On Belle Isle.

03:29.034 --> 03:30.862
And I need to get it
to someone.

03:30.906 --> 03:32.081
A woman and a child.

03:32.124 --> 03:33.735
No one is going anywhere.

03:33.778 --> 03:35.911
Certainly not back to the
scene of what happened.

03:35.954 --> 03:38.783
And families aren't being
notified until we know more.

03:38.827 --> 03:40.220
How about this?

03:40.263 --> 03:42.570
You give me their names,

03:42.613 --> 03:44.746
and I'll see if I can locate
this woman and child.

03:44.789 --> 03:47.227
And in return...

03:47.270 --> 03:49.098
you tell me everything you know

03:49.141 --> 03:50.534
about how you got here.

03:50.578 --> 03:52.580
And Belle Isle?

03:54.277 --> 03:56.192
We'll see.

03:56.236 --> 03:58.586
First, Shanice Murray.

03:58.629 --> 04:00.501
She escaped.

04:00.544 --> 04:02.503
I think she knows more
than she's letting on.

04:02.546 --> 04:04.896
Well...

04:04.940 --> 04:07.377
everyone has secrets.

04:07.421 --> 04:09.118
♪ If I never...

04:09.161 --> 04:11.033
Sure you can't stay any longer?

04:11.076 --> 04:12.600
I'm on the swing shift later.

04:12.643 --> 04:14.210
I'd love to.

04:14.254 --> 04:16.168
But I've got to get back.

04:16.212 --> 04:19.259
My father has me
leading the service today.

04:19.302 --> 04:21.783
Guess you haven't told them yet?

04:21.826 --> 04:23.872
I...

04:23.915 --> 04:26.178
I'm just waiting
for the right moment.

04:26.222 --> 04:28.050
I want to make sure
they really understand.

04:28.093 --> 04:30.139
Understand why their precious,
perfect baby boy

04:30.182 --> 04:31.662
would end up
with someone like me?

04:31.706 --> 04:34.012
Darlene... it's not like that.

04:34.056 --> 04:36.232
I'm going on 17 weeks now.

04:36.276 --> 04:38.452
You said you wanted
to keep it.

04:38.495 --> 04:40.628
That you wanted us
to do this together.I do!

04:40.671 --> 04:42.325
Because I can't afford
a baby on my own.

04:42.369 --> 04:44.284
You're not on your own.

04:44.327 --> 04:46.329
I'm with you.

04:46.373 --> 04:48.462
I thank the Lord
every day

04:48.505 --> 04:50.333
He brought you
to me, Darlene.

04:50.377 --> 04:53.815
But they've got their
old ways of thinking.

04:53.858 --> 04:56.470
I've got to show them
that they're wrong.

04:58.254 --> 05:01.170
You trust me, right?

05:01.213 --> 05:03.390
Yeah.

05:03.433 --> 05:05.783
Yeah?Yeah...

05:05.827 --> 05:08.395
♪ About the love
that you made... ♪

05:08.438 --> 05:10.179
Do you really think
intimidation tactics

05:10.222 --> 05:11.789
like those interrogations
are gonna work?

05:11.833 --> 05:14.139
We have to use
every tactic we can.

05:14.183 --> 05:16.403
Keisha, they are scared.Shanice Murray escaped.

05:16.446 --> 05:18.230
Yes, because they're being
locked up here for no reason.

05:18.274 --> 05:19.841
Well, I want to know
who she's working with.

05:19.884 --> 05:21.669
Where's this
I.T. guy anyway?

05:21.712 --> 05:22.931
SORAYA:
Present!

05:22.974 --> 05:24.715
And she wasn't
working with anyone.

05:24.759 --> 05:26.064
That's what I wanted
to show you.

05:26.108 --> 05:28.110
Uh, Keisha and Jharrel, right?

05:28.153 --> 05:29.372
Cool to meet you.

05:29.416 --> 05:31.331
I'm Soraya. Texpert.
[chuckles]

05:31.374 --> 05:33.376
You like that?
I'm making it a thing.

05:33.420 --> 05:35.726
They hired me to shore up
the security in this place,

05:35.770 --> 05:37.598
which is, yeah, lacking.

05:37.641 --> 05:39.600
But look.

05:39.643 --> 05:41.863
Here's the footage from the
cameras where Shanice escaped.

05:41.906 --> 05:44.431
Okay, we've seen this footage.
Seems like the doors just...

05:44.474 --> 05:45.910
opened.

05:45.954 --> 05:47.434
Then someone moved
the cameras remotely,

05:47.477 --> 05:49.392
so we can't see
how she opened the door.

05:49.436 --> 05:51.655
No. Her body language says that
she wasn't prepared for this.

05:51.699 --> 05:53.570
Wasn't planning on escaping.

05:53.614 --> 05:55.224
She took advantage
of a door opening.

05:55.267 --> 05:57.052
Are you a body language
expert, too?

05:57.095 --> 05:59.184
Oh, I watch a lot
of reality television.

05:59.228 --> 06:00.751
People say it's
trash, but...

06:00.795 --> 06:02.274
I say it's a masterclass
on human nature.

06:02.318 --> 06:03.841
So we're listening
to a specialist

06:03.885 --> 06:05.930
that trained
in the Ex-Wivesfranchise?

06:05.974 --> 06:09.369
Uh... technically I went
to M.I.T. and Quantico, too.

06:09.412 --> 06:11.458
But that was a
lot more boring.

06:11.501 --> 06:13.155
What's not boring is this gig.

06:13.198 --> 06:14.896
Had to get clearance
to take it, but...

06:14.939 --> 06:18.247
[whoops] I had no idea
it would be... this.

06:18.290 --> 06:20.118
Yeah, and what is this?

06:20.162 --> 06:21.555
Because I can't get
anything real out of them.

06:21.598 --> 06:22.643
Well, it's clear they have

06:22.686 --> 06:24.384
no idea what happened to them.

06:24.427 --> 06:26.429
Which is consistent with
reportings of alien encounters.

06:26.473 --> 06:28.388
Aliens? Seriously?

06:28.431 --> 06:30.999
Maybe? But the
simplest explanation

06:31.042 --> 06:34.002
is that they time travelled,
clearly against their will.

06:34.045 --> 06:36.831
So... who did that to them?

06:36.874 --> 06:38.920
I'm sorry, time travel is
the simplest explanation?

06:38.963 --> 06:40.965
Except time travel isn't
a thing.

06:41.009 --> 06:43.054
Mm.
So what's
the logical explanation?

06:43.098 --> 06:45.622
Well, it is illogical to think
that we have all the tools

06:45.666 --> 06:48.320
or the means to explain
everything in the universe.

06:48.364 --> 06:50.410
So...

06:50.453 --> 06:52.281
why didn't we let Shanice Murray
have a minute to catch up

06:52.324 --> 06:54.414
with her family after she
was cleared by medical?

06:54.457 --> 06:55.937
That is a great question.

06:55.980 --> 06:58.113
Good point...

06:58.156 --> 06:59.767
about the family.

06:59.810 --> 07:01.769
We cleared the husband
after her visit, but...

07:01.812 --> 07:04.293
maybe he can get something
out of her that I can't.

07:04.336 --> 07:06.382
Maybe she'll tell him
what she knows.

07:08.645 --> 07:10.691
Yo, what's her deal?

07:10.734 --> 07:12.606
Is she single?

07:12.649 --> 07:13.781
[chuckles]

07:14.782 --> 07:15.826
[doorbell rings]

07:16.914 --> 07:18.655
[sighs]

07:21.745 --> 07:23.878
I'm just here to talk.

07:27.708 --> 07:29.318
We, uh...

07:29.361 --> 07:30.754
we saw on the news.

07:30.798 --> 07:32.887
Is that what
Shanice is a part of?

07:32.930 --> 07:34.628
That 4,400 people?

07:34.671 --> 07:36.630
So you didn't have
anything to do

07:36.673 --> 07:37.935
with leaking it to the press?

07:37.979 --> 07:39.546
Leak what?
I don't know anything.

07:39.589 --> 07:42.157
Shanice just shows up
at my doorstep after being gone

07:42.200 --> 07:43.637
16 years,

07:43.680 --> 07:45.160
talking like she just left.

07:45.203 --> 07:47.510
The government is...
trying to figure it out.

07:47.554 --> 07:49.643
Okay, we're trying to help.

07:50.731 --> 07:53.037
Is, uh...

07:53.081 --> 07:55.126
is she okay?

07:55.170 --> 07:58.086
She's... angry.

07:58.129 --> 08:00.175
Reciting the Michigan Penal Code

08:00.218 --> 08:02.264
nonstop.

08:02.307 --> 08:04.396
Yeah, it sounds like Shanice.

08:06.573 --> 08:09.010
Listen, I'll admit
that I can't get through to her.

08:09.053 --> 08:11.578
I want to try to figure out
what's going on.

08:11.621 --> 08:13.449
I want to help her.

08:13.493 --> 08:15.320
She won't talk to me.

08:16.931 --> 08:18.715
But maybe she'll talk to you.

08:18.759 --> 08:20.717
No. No, no, no.

08:20.761 --> 08:23.067
No, listen,
we can't be involved.

08:23.111 --> 08:25.156
You know, I have a daughter
I have to think about.

08:25.200 --> 08:27.202
And that's a big part
of the reason I'm here.

08:27.245 --> 08:29.770
I don't think you
or your family has anything

08:29.813 --> 08:32.424
to do with this, but it would
go a long way in easing

08:32.468 --> 08:34.252
everyone's mind if you help.

08:36.820 --> 08:39.214
LADONNA:
Uh-uh, I'm not doing it.

08:39.257 --> 08:41.782
I already lost a nail in here
and it's probably from cutting

08:41.825 --> 08:44.785
your arm open over and over
again-- Doc, tell her.

08:44.828 --> 08:46.700
This does not
seem wise.

08:46.743 --> 08:48.789
I swore an oath
to first do no harm.

08:48.832 --> 08:51.052
And that is Doc talk
for "it's cray."

08:51.095 --> 08:53.445
Don't you want to know
the limits of this thing?

08:53.489 --> 08:55.360
What exactly
I can take?

08:55.404 --> 08:57.711
Lord have mercy--
just break my finger!

08:58.886 --> 09:00.757
We already know I
can heal from cuts.

09:00.801 --> 09:03.412
If I can heal from anything...

09:03.455 --> 09:06.241
I can isolate one of them guards
and take 'em on.

09:06.284 --> 09:09.549
And then if they beat me
or shoot me...

09:09.592 --> 09:12.247
whatever... I can withstand it

09:12.290 --> 09:14.336
and escape and figure out

09:14.379 --> 09:16.120
how to get everyone out.

09:16.164 --> 09:18.079
Well...

09:18.122 --> 09:21.561
experimentation and observation
are the best road

09:21.604 --> 09:23.214
to discovery.
Yes.

09:23.258 --> 09:24.912
Y'all are really kind
of demented, you know that?

09:24.955 --> 09:27.044
Uh... [chuckles]

09:27.088 --> 09:29.090
Never mind, Doc,
Ladonna here just...

09:29.133 --> 09:30.700
just doesn't have
the stomach for it.

09:30.744 --> 09:32.397
Now I didn't take her
for a fraidy cat...

09:32.441 --> 09:34.486
Whoa, I'm not afraid
of anything, okay?

09:34.530 --> 09:36.532
You're just-just too weak

09:36.576 --> 09:37.968
to get the job done, dear--
it's fine.

09:38.012 --> 09:39.491
Excuse me?
[scoffs]

09:39.535 --> 09:41.581
Look, I once took out
a backstabbing skank

09:41.624 --> 09:44.061
with one four-inch stiletto
to the chin, so I am not weak.

09:44.105 --> 09:46.324
I didn't quite follow all that--
pray tell, what is a skank?

09:46.368 --> 09:47.587
Prove it.

09:50.198 --> 09:51.721
Oh!Miss Ladonna!

09:51.765 --> 09:53.114
She made me.

09:53.157 --> 09:54.463
[whimpering]

09:54.506 --> 09:56.552
[grunting]

10:03.559 --> 10:05.126
Fascinating.

10:05.169 --> 10:06.649
[laughing]: It worked!Oh, my God.

10:06.693 --> 10:08.738
Whoa.

10:08.782 --> 10:10.087
[alarm sounding][gasps]

10:10.131 --> 10:12.002
Hmm?
GUARD:
Count! Count!

10:12.046 --> 10:13.700
GUARD: Line 'em up!GUARD 2: All right,
let's line up!

10:13.743 --> 10:15.179
KEN:
Okay, everybody, listen up!

10:15.223 --> 10:17.529
Moving forward,
we'll be doing counts.

10:17.573 --> 10:20.620
This group is assigned to this
checkpoint. When you hear

10:20.663 --> 10:22.926
the alarm, you have
two minutes to get here.

10:22.970 --> 10:25.668
You're being fitted
with GPS ankle bands.

10:25.712 --> 10:29.324
Just in case anyone gets any
bright ideas about sneaking out.

10:29.367 --> 10:31.282
Again.

10:31.326 --> 10:34.329
These measures are in place for
you and everyone else's safety.

10:34.372 --> 10:36.723
Do we understand each other?

10:36.766 --> 10:39.726
♪ This little light of mine...

10:39.769 --> 10:40.988
Do you think this is funny?

10:41.031 --> 10:42.598
N-No.Then shut your mouth.

10:42.642 --> 10:43.686
[stammers]

10:43.730 --> 10:45.645
Oh, we know about you already.

10:46.558 --> 10:47.647
Got something to say?

10:56.481 --> 10:58.005
SHANICE:
Why am I back here?

10:58.048 --> 11:00.442
Why won't you guys tell me

11:00.485 --> 11:01.965
what's going on?

11:02.009 --> 11:03.053
[gasps]

11:03.097 --> 11:04.272
Logan?

11:04.315 --> 11:05.969
Hi, Shanice.

11:11.496 --> 11:14.891
So, uh...

11:14.935 --> 11:16.240
this is where you've been.

11:16.284 --> 11:18.286
Well, just for
the last few days.

11:18.329 --> 11:20.984
Be... fore that I was home

11:21.028 --> 11:22.943
and then...Right, you, uh...

11:22.986 --> 11:26.250
you somehow don't remember what
happened for the past 16 years.

11:26.294 --> 11:29.471
Do I look
like I've aged 16 years?

11:29.514 --> 11:31.778
[both laugh]

11:31.821 --> 11:34.171
You know, this place reminds me
of that hotel we stayed at.

11:34.215 --> 11:36.434
Up north.Yeah.

11:36.478 --> 11:38.567
When we had to have
the house fumigated.

11:38.610 --> 11:40.656
Mm-hmm.[both chuckle]

11:42.092 --> 11:44.747
Still can't believe you
shelled out for that trip.

11:44.791 --> 11:46.618
You were
six months pregnant, Shanice.

11:46.662 --> 11:47.968
What, I'm gonna
make you sleep

11:48.011 --> 11:50.187
on Mrs. Grover's
guest bed?

11:50.231 --> 11:52.059
It's like sleeping
on a slab of concrete.

11:52.102 --> 11:54.322
[both laugh]

11:58.718 --> 12:00.067
Why did you come?

12:01.111 --> 12:03.461
You really don't know
what happened?

12:03.505 --> 12:06.334
I only know that I didn't leave.

12:07.857 --> 12:10.947
Yes, I thought about
leaving at one point.

12:10.991 --> 12:13.471
It was postpartum depression.

12:13.515 --> 12:16.779
It was bad and I had
some... dark nights.

12:16.823 --> 12:19.303
You wrote me
a goodbye note, Shanice.

12:22.350 --> 12:24.613
I mean, I-I knew
it was hard, but I...

12:25.570 --> 12:27.485
You never told me.

12:27.529 --> 12:29.270
I didn't know how.

12:29.313 --> 12:31.272
How was I supposed
to tell you that?

12:31.315 --> 12:33.840
I would've helped, I would've.

12:34.971 --> 12:36.756
But you were never good
at asking for help.

12:41.761 --> 12:43.719
Yeah, well, can I...?

12:43.763 --> 12:46.156
Will you bring Mariah?

12:46.200 --> 12:48.898
I'd like to...

12:48.942 --> 12:50.595
I guess, meet her.

12:50.639 --> 12:52.336
Get to know her.

12:53.337 --> 12:54.991
I don't think
that's a good idea.

12:55.035 --> 12:56.819
