at His command.

27:10.193 --> 27:11.499
Maybe.

27:11.542 --> 27:14.197
But now we use it for us.

27:14.241 --> 27:17.418
If that's what you see,
then you are lost in your faith.

27:17.461 --> 27:20.595
Every day we preach the Word
to those people out there,

27:20.639 --> 27:22.553
because they are tired,

27:22.597 --> 27:24.904
they are sad, anxious,

27:24.947 --> 27:26.732
in pain,
because the world is hard.

27:26.775 --> 27:28.690
I know that...You don't know!

27:28.734 --> 27:30.344
You don't know
or you wouldn't be standing here

27:30.387 --> 27:32.128
giving me this nonsense.

27:32.172 --> 27:34.174
The Lord asked
us, this family,

27:34.217 --> 27:35.523
to sacrifice.

27:35.566 --> 27:37.830
To dedicate our lives to others.

27:37.873 --> 27:41.181
They need to see that the
Lord put us here for them.

27:41.224 --> 27:43.400
They need to see
that we can bear their burdens

27:43.444 --> 27:45.664
and that there are
rewards beyond the material.

27:45.707 --> 27:47.535
Because what people need--

27:47.578 --> 27:49.711
what the Lord knows they need--

27:49.755 --> 27:51.234
is hope.

27:53.149 --> 27:55.717
And if you don't know
that that's worth more

27:55.761 --> 27:58.154
than dollars and cents...

28:00.156 --> 28:02.419
...then you really
don't understand, son.

28:02.463 --> 28:04.204
Who do you
think you are?

28:04.247 --> 28:06.641
That you can reject God's plan?

28:06.685 --> 28:08.382
Hmm?

28:11.341 --> 28:13.300
[scoffs]

28:22.831 --> 28:24.920
♪

28:25.965 --> 28:27.227
NOAH:
It was stupid.

28:27.270 --> 28:28.968
It's not stupid.

28:29.011 --> 28:31.579
It's what everyone needs.
I see that now.

28:31.622 --> 28:33.755
It's my calling.

28:33.799 --> 28:35.801
I haven't been listening.

28:35.844 --> 28:39.195
Listening to who?You have my promise, Noah.

28:39.239 --> 28:40.806
I'm going to make things right.

28:40.849 --> 28:43.591
But first I need to know
everything that's going on.

28:43.634 --> 28:45.549
I feel like there's things
that I don't know about.

28:45.593 --> 28:47.029
Like with the singing.

28:49.815 --> 28:50.729
Will you share with me?

28:54.820 --> 28:56.256
[knocking]

28:58.562 --> 29:00.303
Hey there.

29:00.347 --> 29:02.305
I heard there
was an incident

29:02.349 --> 29:04.133
with one of the guards?

29:06.309 --> 29:07.833
Wanted to check on you.

29:07.876 --> 29:09.486
And...

29:09.530 --> 29:11.097
uh, bring you some food.

29:12.098 --> 29:13.708
Made it myself.

29:14.840 --> 29:16.319
Since...

29:16.363 --> 29:17.930
uh, you said
you didn't like the food.

29:17.973 --> 29:19.496
What about my friend?

29:19.540 --> 29:21.455
The guards are here
for your protection.

29:21.498 --> 29:22.456
[scoffs]

29:22.499 --> 29:23.674
When any of you disobeys

29:23.718 --> 29:24.937
the rules, it...

29:24.980 --> 29:26.765
makes things unsafe
for everyone.

29:26.808 --> 29:28.941
We're not safe now.

29:28.984 --> 29:30.420
How can we be when
we're not free?!

29:37.993 --> 29:39.995
[indistinct chatter]

29:40.039 --> 29:42.432
Hey.
Yo.

29:42.476 --> 29:44.434
So...

29:44.478 --> 29:45.827
why did you want me
to meet you here?

29:45.871 --> 29:47.655
Wanted to talk somewhere

29:47.698 --> 29:49.483
without cameras tracking
our every move.

29:52.094 --> 29:54.096
I think we should take people
back to Belle Isle.

29:54.140 --> 29:55.968
Okay...

29:56.011 --> 29:59.058
I-I've heard rumblings
among the 4,400 about this,

29:59.101 --> 30:01.277
but youwant to do this?

30:01.321 --> 30:03.410
Some of these people seem
to be doing badly here.

30:03.453 --> 30:05.499
If we can show them that
we're trying to help them...

30:05.542 --> 30:07.109
Mm-hmm, and who knows,

30:07.153 --> 30:08.632
maybe they're right,
and Belle Isle is some kind

30:08.676 --> 30:10.460
of time machine.Funny.

30:10.504 --> 30:12.854
I will be watching every minute,
see if we can get some clues,

30:12.898 --> 30:15.770
some idea of... what happened
last time they were there.

30:15.814 --> 30:17.380
And I am going to enjoy

30:17.424 --> 30:19.208
seeing these people
actually get some fresh air.

30:20.514 --> 30:22.516
Whatever happens,
they deserve that.

30:22.559 --> 30:25.171
So... you gonna sweet-talk
your girl into it?

30:26.215 --> 30:28.130
I will handle Agent Tanner.

30:28.174 --> 30:30.437
She got called
to oversee an emergency

30:30.480 --> 30:32.569
at the Ypsi Med facility.

30:32.613 --> 30:34.180
Took a bunch of the guards
with her,

30:34.223 --> 30:36.269
so the place is as unguarded
as it will ever be.

30:36.312 --> 30:38.227
[chuckles]

30:38.271 --> 30:40.360
Okay, night trip to Belle Isle

30:40.403 --> 30:41.796
it is, but you and me

30:41.840 --> 30:43.406
can't take everybody.

30:43.450 --> 30:45.974
Maybe we can slip a group out
after their count.

30:46.018 --> 30:47.889
Mm, and they're all wearing
ankle monitors,

30:47.933 --> 30:50.239
so we'll be able find them
if anything goes wrong.

30:50.283 --> 30:53.155
But... I have my body-worn
camera just in case.

30:53.199 --> 30:54.896
Yes, yes,
everyone will be tracked

30:54.940 --> 30:56.593
and monitored
within an inch of their life.

30:56.637 --> 30:58.334
A police state
in action.
Hey.

30:59.248 --> 31:00.771
We stay vigilant.

31:00.815 --> 31:02.077
Okay?

31:07.648 --> 31:09.128
Ah.

31:09.171 --> 31:10.999
Me and my brother used to
draw these everywhere.

31:11.043 --> 31:13.001
It was a game to play.

31:13.045 --> 31:15.830
One of us would start out a
clock, the other one would add

31:15.874 --> 31:17.745
another number and we'd...

31:17.788 --> 31:19.616
keep adding numbers
until it was done.

31:19.660 --> 31:21.444
Think he might still be here?

31:22.663 --> 31:25.057
I don't know, these people
arriving here, they...

31:25.100 --> 31:27.537
brought back my hope
for finding him.

31:28.495 --> 31:30.801
So if...

31:30.845 --> 31:33.892
somehow this whole thing
works out...

31:33.935 --> 31:36.677
and they do go back, then...

31:38.070 --> 31:40.376
I don't know, maybe I can put
this whole thing behind me.

31:41.377 --> 31:43.118
Finally let go of Manny, too.

31:46.252 --> 31:47.514
To Belle Isle.

31:55.348 --> 31:56.784
Hey.

31:56.827 --> 31:59.221
I heard you earlier.

31:59.265 --> 32:01.136
I-I hope this helps you
feel better.

32:01.180 --> 32:02.964
That you'll be out,
free for a bit.

32:03.008 --> 32:04.183
Oh, I'm not going.

32:04.226 --> 32:06.446
I have to stay here.

32:06.489 --> 32:08.361
But why? I-I thought...Are you sure?

32:09.405 --> 32:12.104
I just have to stay... here.

32:12.147 --> 32:14.758
See you when we get back?

32:14.802 --> 32:16.717
Yeah.

32:24.681 --> 32:26.727
♪

32:28.120 --> 32:30.122
[indistinct chatter]

32:39.174 --> 32:40.523
So...

32:40.567 --> 32:43.352
you notice anything
suspicious?

32:43.396 --> 32:45.964
I mean, have you figured
out the mystery yet?

32:46.007 --> 32:47.748
[exhales]

32:47.791 --> 32:49.315
Guess the time machine's
not working tonight.

32:49.358 --> 32:50.446
[chuckles]

33:05.287 --> 33:07.072
That's what you wanted
to come back here for?

33:07.115 --> 33:09.726
Originally, yes.

33:11.815 --> 33:13.121
Nice rock.

33:13.165 --> 33:14.688
Worth a pretty penny.

33:14.731 --> 33:17.082
It is. I was gonna
give it to Darlene

33:17.125 --> 33:19.998
to show her that I had always
intended to do right by her.

33:20.041 --> 33:22.261
I tracked her down,
her and her son.

33:23.479 --> 33:24.524
Your son?

33:25.525 --> 33:27.048
A son?

33:27.092 --> 33:28.702
I have a son?

33:30.356 --> 33:32.706
I have to let them go.

33:32.749 --> 33:34.099
But why... [laughs]

33:34.142 --> 33:36.057
It's not what the
Lord wanted for me.

33:36.101 --> 33:37.841
I made the wrong choice then.

33:37.885 --> 33:40.192
And I think
that's why this is happening.

33:40.235 --> 33:41.889
He is showing me

33:41.932 --> 33:44.326
the way-- that I must
accept my calling.

33:44.370 --> 33:45.849
What calling?

33:45.893 --> 33:47.503
To be here.

33:47.547 --> 33:50.028
To be present. To believe.

33:50.071 --> 33:53.814
Mark 9:23--
"All things are possible

33:53.857 --> 33:55.511
to him that believeth."

33:55.555 --> 33:58.079
If you'll excuse me, I'd...

33:58.123 --> 34:00.777
like to lead a prayer.

34:03.476 --> 34:05.173
[exhales]

34:07.393 --> 34:09.003
First, let's take a moment

34:09.047 --> 34:10.787
to give thanks for being here.

34:10.831 --> 34:12.920
Lord, the fresh air feels good.

34:12.963 --> 34:16.141
It's strange being back
in this place, isn't it?

34:16.184 --> 34:18.360
What we've gone through

34:18.404 --> 34:21.407
is a lot for any human to bear,
and they try

34:21.450 --> 34:24.018
and they try
to take our humanity away,

34:24.062 --> 34:25.802
but they won't succeed.

34:27.587 --> 34:32.070
♪ Hush little baby
don't say a word ♪

34:32.113 --> 34:36.639
♪ Mama's gonna buy you
a mocking bird... ♪

34:36.683 --> 34:39.425
We were taken away
from the comfort of our lives,♪ And if that mocking

34:39.468 --> 34:41.644
taken from those we love,♪ Bird don't sing

34:41.688 --> 34:43.516
taken from♪ Mama's gonna

34:43.559 --> 34:45.344
our realities as we knew it!♪ Buy you a diamond ring

34:45.387 --> 34:47.433
And...♪ And if

34:47.476 --> 34:49.130
some of you came here tonight♪ That diamond ring

34:49.174 --> 34:50.958
hoping to make that all go away.♪ Turns brass

34:51.001 --> 34:53.917
I'm here to tell you♪ Mama's gonna buy you

34:53.961 --> 34:55.658
it won't.♪ A looking glass

34:55.702 --> 34:57.530
We must accept the truth

34:57.573 --> 34:59.140
of our tribulations.[Noah continues singing]

34:59.184 --> 35:01.708
We must accept the seriousness

35:01.751 --> 35:04.145
of our circumstance,
because the truth is,

35:04.189 --> 35:07.670
we were brought
forward in time, yes?

35:07.714 --> 35:09.759
But the Lord didn't
bring us here[others murmuring]

35:09.803 --> 35:11.283
to flounder alone.

35:11.326 --> 35:13.111
He gave us each other.

35:13.154 --> 35:14.590
♪ ...buy you
a cart and bull... ♪

35:14.634 --> 35:16.549
And he gave us gifts.

35:16.592 --> 35:19.639
♪ And if that cart and bull...

35:20.596 --> 35:23.033
[gasping]

35:25.384 --> 35:28.082
[indistinct chatter]

35:28.126 --> 35:31.216
Let's give praise
to Sister Mildred.

35:31.259 --> 35:33.957
She's making this happen
with her mind.

35:34.001 --> 35:36.656
And Brother Noah is
using his voice

35:36.699 --> 35:38.832
to give us the privacy
of this moment.

35:38.875 --> 35:41.051
Just us...
without our keepers.

35:42.140 --> 35:44.272
They're fine, just in slumber.

35:44.316 --> 35:46.796
Because I needed
this moment to reach you,

35:46.840 --> 35:50.235
to let you all know
that you're special.

35:50.278 --> 35:52.889
To let you all know
that we've been taken

35:52.933 --> 35:55.936
and brought here for a reason.

35:55.979 --> 35:59.069
We have been brought here
on a mission!

35:59.113 --> 36:02.725
We don't know
exactly what it is yet.

36:02.769 --> 36:05.598
But I believe
that I am here to lead you.

36:05.641 --> 36:07.208
[others murmuring]

36:07.252 --> 36:09.123
Look within yourself.

36:09.167 --> 36:11.952
See yourself
and know your worth.

36:11.995 --> 36:15.521
Know your power
and own your gifts.

36:15.564 --> 36:17.305
Because who are we

36:17.349 --> 36:19.916
to question God's plan?

36:20.874 --> 36:22.223
Extraordinary.

36:22.267 --> 36:24.443
I assumed there were others,

36:24.486 --> 36:26.096
but I never imagined

36:26.140 --> 36:27.576
this.

36:27.620 --> 36:29.143
I just thought finally
maybe it was my turn

36:29.187 --> 36:31.493
to be the one people turn to.

36:31.537 --> 36:32.842
But him.

36:34.583 --> 36:36.585
Give him another two weeks,
and they'll be

36:36.629 --> 36:39.022
eating out
of the palm of his hand.

36:39.066 --> 36:40.807
And I do not trust
what he will do

36:40.850 --> 36:42.852
with that kind of power.

36:50.295 --> 36:52.645
Well... they didn't
get taken back.

36:52.688 --> 36:55.082
Instead we all just,
what, fell asleep?

36:55.125 --> 36:56.475
Something put us to sleep.

36:56.518 --> 36:58.912
Something put everybody
on Belle Isle

36:58.955 --> 37:00.914
to sleep at the same time.

37:00.957 --> 37:02.437
The question is: what?

37:02.481 --> 37:03.960
The 4,400 seemed
just as confused

37:04.004 --> 37:05.310
as we were
when all of us woke up.

37:05.353 --> 37:07.007
No, we don't know
what happened to them.

37:07.050 --> 37:08.617
We were asleep.

37:08.661 --> 37:10.271
Okay, well, we know
that they all got on the bus

37:10.315 --> 37:12.578
with us just as planned.

37:12.621 --> 37:14.667
Everyone accounted for.
No trouble at all.

37:14.710 --> 37:16.364
What, you think
they were faking it?

37:16.408 --> 37:18.061
I think I'm gonna find out.

37:18.105 --> 37:19.933
Pulling up the footage
from my body cam right now.

37:19.976 --> 37:22.196
Score one for our police state,
by the way.

37:22.240 --> 37:24.416
Ah, cop's got jokes.

37:24.459 --> 37:26.026
At least we can
actually see what...

37:26.069 --> 37:27.462
happened.

37:27.506 --> 37:30.596
So, I took
the ankle bracelets off-line

37:30.639 --> 37:33.251
for a little unscheduled
reboot, like you asked.

37:34.208 --> 37:36.471
But I'm dying
to know what happened.

37:36.515 --> 37:38.038
Was it like an Outlander
kind of situation

37:38.081 --> 37:39.605
or, like, more
like Close Encounters?

37:39.648 --> 37:42.651
I'm still not sure
why you're even helping us.

37:43.957 --> 37:46.089
I don't like this whole
operation.

37:46.133 --> 37:47.961
From what I can tell,

37:48.004 --> 37:49.789
these people shouldn't be
locked up.

37:49.832 --> 37:52.139
And even if they are
aliens or clones

37:52.182 --> 37:54.228
or run-of-the-mill
time travelers,

37:54.272 --> 37:56.535
those things aren't even crimes.

37:59.015 --> 38:01.191
So if you two are
trying to help them,

38:01.235 --> 38:02.976
I'll help you.

38:04.194 --> 38:05.587
Oh, come on.

38:05.631 --> 38:07.154
We should show her.

38:12.725 --> 38:14.770
[playback accelerated]

38:16.381 --> 38:20.167
NOAH: ♪ Hush little baby,
don't say a word ♪

38:20.210 --> 38:22.909
♪ Mama's gonna buy you...

38:22.952 --> 38:24.345
Damn it, the camera broke.

38:24.389 --> 38:25.955
Like, what happened?
Was there some kind

38:25.999 --> 38:27.479
of sonic weapon
that put everyone to sleep?

38:27.522 --> 38:29.568
Or is it the atmosphere
on Belle Isle?

38:29.611 --> 38:31.265
I don't know.

38:31.309 --> 38:33.006
But I want
to find out.

38:33.049 --> 38:35.182
Let me go back to the office,
and see if I can pull

38:35.225 --> 38:37.576
anything else from the footage.
You coming?

38:37.619 --> 38:38.838
I can't.

38:38.881 --> 38:40.970
Got to go lie to my girlfriend.

38:41.014 --> 38:42.711
I'll send you
the file.

38:43.669 --> 38:44.844
[whispers]:
Girlfriend?

38:45.975 --> 38:47.325
[scoffs softly]

38:49.152 --> 38:52.373
["Meet Me in the Mystery"
by Lissie playing]

38:52.417 --> 38:55.985
♪ I wanna know the secret

38:56.029 --> 38:59.641
♪ I am ready to let go

38:59.685 --> 39:03.776
♪ Get me out of the familiar

39:03.819 --> 39:05.081
♪ I wanna know...

39:05.125 --> 39:06.344
BARTENDER:
Care for a drink?

39:06.387 --> 39:08.041
No thanks.
I'm waiting for my lady.

39:08.084 --> 39:09.608
That for her?

39:09.651 --> 39:11.914
In a way.

39:11.958 --> 39:14.526
This is the key
to our future together.

39:14.569 --> 39:16.571
Worth a fortune.

39:16.615 --> 39:18.660
I'll be able to give her
everything she needs,

39:18.704 --> 39:20.923
everything she deserves
with this.

39:20.967 --> 39:22.751
It's the start
of our life together.

39:22.795 --> 39:24.492
That looks heavy.

39:24.536 --> 39:26.364
I think something like that
might weigh me down.

39:26.407 --> 39:28.235
Me, too.

39:28.278 --> 39:32.108
It would tempt me into becoming
someone I didn't want to be.

39:33.283 --> 39:35.329
And that's
why I'm never gonna wear it.

39:37.070 --> 39:39.028
I'm gonna be free.

39:39.072 --> 39:41.248
We're gonna be free.

39:43.598 --> 39:45.557
If she comes looking for me,

39:45.600 --> 39:47.036
can you tell her
I'll be right back?

39:47.080 --> 39:48.386
Sure thing.

39:48.429 --> 39:50.083
Thank you.

39:52.912 --> 39:55.088
♪

39:55.131 --> 39:57.307
[zapping]

40:10.625 --> 40:12.453
Excu...?
He just went
to the restroom.

40:12.497 --> 40:13.933
But he'll be
right back.

40:13.976 --> 40:15.848
Great. I'll wait.

40:15.891 --> 40:18.111
♪ Meet me in the mystery

40:18.154 --> 40:21.680
♪ Meet me in the hollow

40:21.723 --> 40:25.901
♪ Teach me, I am listening

40:25.945 --> 40:27.947
♪ Lead and I will

40:27.990 --> 40:31.211
♪ Follow...

40:32.560 --> 40:34.954
ANDRE:
That ended up being
a rather eventful evening.

40:34.997 --> 40:37.391
I guess I kind of got
wrapped up in the idea

40:37.435 --> 40:38.871
that it was gonna be
more eventful.

40:38.914 --> 40:40.960
That we'd return.

40:42.440 --> 40:44.703
I, too, am sad
for what we lost.

40:44.746 --> 40:47.009
But what we've
all gone through,

40:47.053 --> 40:49.751
it's truly awe-inspiring
and...

40:51.536 --> 40:54.016
...I'm also grateful

40:54.060 --> 40:56.105
for what I have found here.

40:59.369 --> 41:01.415
Me, too, Doc.

41:01.459 --> 41:03.809
[clears throat] So...

41:03.852 --> 41:06.333
uh, I think we continue to be

41:06.376 --> 41:07.813
in a confounding situation.

41:07.856 --> 41:10.250
As to what that heralds
for our future,

41:10.293 --> 41:12.165
I...

41:12.208 --> 41:13.558
cannot say.

41:16.604 --> 41:18.693
Perhaps it will become
clearer in the morning.

41:18.737 --> 41:20.434
Perhaps.

41:20.478 --> 41:21.740
Good night.

41:29.661 --> 41:31.619
Hi, Mom.

41:31.663 --> 41:33.273
♪ Meet me in the hollow

41:33.316 --> 41:34.883
All right, I'll be
right back, Soraya.

41:34.927 --> 41:38.147
♪ Teach me, I am listening

41:38.191 --> 41:41.716
♪ Lead and I will follow

41:48.375 --> 41:51.509
♪ I am ready for the darkness

41:54.381 --> 41:57.515
♪ I am ready to let go.

